-- Deutsche Bourse Starts Euro-Priced Gold in London
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2010-09-28T13:06:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/deutsche-bourse-starts-euro-priced-gold-in-london-update1-.html
The Deutsche Bourse is starting a
euro-priced gold contract in London today, also known as Xetra-
Gold, for trading over-the-counter, said  Steffen Orben , managing
director of commodities at the exchange.  Deutsche Bank AG  is the main underwriter, market maker and
sales partner, Orben said in a meeting with reporters in London.
 Commerzbank AG  is a sales partner and market maker, while  DZ
Bank AG ,  Vontobel Holding Ag  and Bankhaus B. Metzler seel Sohn &
Co. KGaA, are also sales partners, said Orben.  Deutsche Bourse first launched its euro-priced gold
contract in Germany in December 2007. It plans to launch the
contract in the Netherlands tomorrow.  Eurex, Europeâ€™s largest derivatives exchange, started
futures and options today on Xetra-Gold, Murat Baygeldi, vice
president of business development at Eurex, said at the same
conference today. Eurex has offered dollar-priced gold futures
and options based on prices from the London Bullion Market
Association since February 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
